msgctxt "an5.203:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.203:0.2"
msgid "21. Kimilavagga "
msgstr "21. With Kimbila "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: ājāniyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.203:0.3"
msgid "203. Assājānīyasutta "
msgstr "203. A Thoroughbred "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: bhadro → bhaddo (pts1)
msgctxt "an5.203:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a fine royal thoroughbred with five factors is worthy of a king, fit to serve a king, and is considered a factor of kingship. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.203:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.203:2.2"
msgid "Ajjavena, javena, maddavena, khantiyā, soraccena—"
msgstr "Integrity, speed, gentleness, patience, and sweetness. "

msgctxt "an5.203:2.3"
msgid "imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño bhadro assājānīyo rājāraho hoti rājabhoggo, rañño aṅgantveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "A fine royal thoroughbred with these five factors is worthy of a king. … "

msgctxt "an5.203:2.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.203:3.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.203:3.2"
msgid "Ajjavena, javena, maddavena, khantiyā, soraccena—"
msgstr "Integrity, speed, gentleness, patience, and sweetness. "

msgctxt "an5.203:3.3"
msgid "imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these five qualities is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.203:3.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

